  "prompt": "If you are deployed on a US submarine and a close relative dies, do they surface and allow you to go home for the funeral?",
  "response": "The decision depends on several factors, including:\n\n1. Mission criticality: If the submarine is on a classified or critical mission, they may not surface or return to port.\n\n2. Location: The submarine's current position and distance from home port can affect the feasibility of returning.\n\n3. Type of operation: Strategic missions might have different protocols compared to routine deployments.\n\nGenerally, the Navy tries to be compassionate, but operational requirements take precedence. Options might include:\n\n- Sending a message of condolence\n- Allowing communication with family\n- Potentially arranging emergency leave at the next port or upon return\n- In some cases, arranging a humanitarian transfer if possible\n\nEach situation is evaluated individually by command leadership, considering the specific circumstances and mission requirements.",
